inn1.comm: good bounce, some away shape, just back of a length, Gayle pulls bat away
closer to the off stump and fuller, straightens, Gayle defends
makes him play with a shortish delivery, Gayle pushes it back
turns a length ball to midwicket to get off the mark
he went for the same delivery that got Charles in the first game, this one's not a full toss, pitches just before it hits Charles on the boot, lbw appeal is turned down

forget Charles, Irfan has struck gold next ball, the big man's taken out the opposition's big man, full delivery outside off, hint of straightening, Gayle pushes loosely, half-heartedly, away from the bodty, and the keeper gladly takes the edge
slight away movement, but the length ball starts wide enough to be left alone
similar ball left alone outside off, good bounce
unconvincing but Charles gets two, tries to slap a length ball down the ground, it loops over the bowler off the toe end

was that an edge, did that carry, Charles was late in pulling the bat away outside off, it did carry low to the keeper, but there isn't much of an appeal from Pakistan, although there was a slight noise as ball passed bat
he is surprised by the bounce on this length ball as it holds the line on middle and leg, stabs it away
plays out a good length ball to the off side
lovely, pitched full for the drive outside off and shapes away sharply, but very late, Bravo lets it go
closer to off and holding its line, he shoulders arms once more
superb line, close to off once again, and the length ball straightens as Bravo leaves it alone
there it is, the previous three swung away, this one came in with the angle, almost took out off stump, after beating the inside edge
just past the man at short leg, Irfan goes on the pads and Bravo tucks him square, in the air but not really a chance, was well wide of the fielder
swings in to the right-hander and hits him high on the pad, going down leg too
length ball not far from off stump, left alone
makes him play with one right on off stump, Bravo defends bat and pad together
wants the single with a soft push in front of point but the fielder is quick to the ball
Bravo slashes as soon as he sees some width, there are shouts of catch it, but it is clear of backward point
not as much width as the previous one, but still Bravo has enough room to slap it through the covers, it's pulled back with a slide near the rope, saves one
now he gives width to the right-hander, Charles moves towards the line and slams it through cover for four more
Irfan continues to exert pressure at the other end, just short of driving length, around off, kicks and straightens past the outside edge
this time he lets a length ball go outside off
that was close, a thick inside edge races past the stumps to fine leg as Bravo pushes away from the body
full and quick on the angle across the right-hander, Charles tries to guide it late, misses
swinging in to the middle stump, Charles right behind it this time, opening up and getting behind the line

almost another one, fine take from Umar Akmal diving in front of first slip, but the ball has not carried, just, Irfan is swinging some in and pushing some across, this one bounced at Charles on off stump, opening him up, had to play at it, a healthy edge but no luck for the bowler
pushes off the front foot to extra cover
blocks a pitched up ball
some away shape ending the back of a length ball on off, defended
overpitched on the stumps, but Bravo cannot clip it past mid on
punches off the back foot, but short extra cover stops it to his right
on middle and leg, good length, pushed back
whoa, Charles clears front leg first ball of the over and swats a low full toss on middle through midwicket
back of a length, bouncing and angling across, left alone
backs away to leg, Irfan follows him with a full delivery, Charles misses the hoick, Irfan walks and stares down from the skies
good length ball bouncing on off, defended softly
opens up and blocks a length ball on off
short-arm swat behind square leg off the hip, Riaz prevents the boundary with some footwork close to the rope
tight line on off stump, defended back to the bowler
middle and leg, good length, Bravo nudges it away
goes full on the stumps, Bravo leans half forward and whips it crisply through midwicket
width outside off on the angle, and Bravo slices it hard over point
on middle, this time Bravo takes it square for a single
opens the face and runs a length ball softly to point
starts down the pads from round the stumps, and is swept in the air to fine leg
quick and fullish, defended off the front foot
there is long on, but Charles has taken him on, charged out, and got enough on the heave to clear the man to his left comfortably
Ajmal tosses it up even more now, but Charles waits in the crease and runs it against the spin to point
pitched up offbreak defended back
uses the good length to come across and work it to deep midwicket
nudges an offbreak off the pad, but backward square leg is there
spins in to the pad again, worked to midwicket
backs away to leg, waits, makes even more room and punches a length offbreak through cover
drives to cover off the front foot
tosses it up on off, Bravo forward to defend

that fooled every one, was angled in, Umar Akmal expected it carry in with the angle and moved to the leg side, but it spun past the outside edge, past the off stump and went for four byes, keeper getting it terribly wrong there
Wahab sprays a full toss a mile outside off, Akmal moves towards slip to take it
pushes forward at a length ball going across and misses it by several inches
pushes forward and drives carefully to extra cover, as if just testing out the pitch after all the rain
walks out and plays out a good length ball to point
pulls the length back and bounces it past a prod from the crease, Charles acknowledges the quality of the delivery, nodding towards the bowler
pushed to extra cover
the ball not doing anything off a good length, played out easily to off
starts superbly with a straightening good length ball outside off, left alone
nice, this one comes in to off stump from over the stumps, Bravo adjusts hurriedly and keeps it out
he'd gone just like this in the first game, strangled down the leg side to a shortish ball angled in, but he's fortunately missed it this time
short, into the body, not too much bite, blocked
trouble, Bravo pushes and charges for a single, Misbah is quick to the ball from extra cover, Bravo turns back late, Misbah is annoyed at missing with the throw
gets on top of a bouncing delivery outside off and dabs it behind point
opens up, gets behind the line and pushes a length ball softly to mid off
overpitched on middle and leg, no swing, Bravo gets bat around pad and clips it through midwicket
moves forward to a pitched up ball outside off and pushes to mid off
gets some width and flashes it out to the sweeper
shortish, Charles bursts into activity late and swats it powerfully to deep square leg
Bravo jumps across to off trying to get behind the line, but this one straightens after pitching back of a length, and pings him on the thigh, painful
behind the line of a length ball this time and pushes to short extra
flashes at a short and wide one leaving him further with the angle, misses
back of a length, much closer, he runs it to point
clears front leg and slogs a length ball, but mishits down to long on
takes a step out, Irfan bangs it in short, Bravo weaves inside the line
is forward, sees it bowled back of a length and plays it softly towards point
that was so close, Bravo driving inside the line of a pitched up delivery, but a free hit is coming up, as Irfan has overstepped
backs away to leg and swings hard, slices a full delivery in the air down to third man
skiddy length ball at 140.8 kph, worked away to short midwicket
not enough room, not much pace off the pitch, and Bravo mishits to extra cover
sharp bouncer, 142.4 kph, Bravo ducks
pitched up on off to follow up after the short ball, he runs it to point
moves away a touch after pitching good length, is guided to point
the ball is not quite coming on, Bravo goes after this length ball that moves away a touch again, but only ends up lifting it without timing towards the sweeper
tight length ball on off stump, can only push it to point
overdoes the yorker by a few inches, Bravo brings down the bat on it just outside off and turns it to the third man boundary
a rare poor delivery from Irfan on the pads, Charles gets enough on it to give the keeper no chance
steers a good length ball with the angle to third man
a solid defensive push to extra cover off the front foot
quick and straightening outside off, played out to point from the crease
legbreak bounces outside off, is punched to the sweeper
92.2 kph and angles down the leg side from round the stumps
has him driving at a pitched up ball, thick edge races past short third man
tosses it up on the stumps, Charles plays it out softly to off
this hurries in with the angle, nearly 97 kph, charles survives with a thick inside edge
this drive was travelling, but so was Misbah, diving to his left at extra cover to snap it up on the bounce, Afridi applauds
length ball at 138 kph on off stump, turned down to third man
he pitches it up, Charles plays in his peculiar manner, staying motionless till very late, then lunging forward and dead-batting it
no room to knock it through the covers, and an underedge goes to the bowler
this time there is width and he uses that to steer it to deep point, sensible batting building a strong partnership
sees width from back of a length and slashes in the air to third man
sends this length ball down leg, but umpire Llong indicates it brushed the leg
he drives it in the air past the short midwicket fielder, loud shout of 'catch' from the bowler, a single to long on

here comes the wicket! Here goes Lala with his arms spread out in self-praise. It was a flighted on, it drifted in and Charles was too early to jump out in a bid to smash it out of the ground. He gets beaten by the flight, beaten by the turn and beaten by the bounce. Easy meal for Afridi as Akmal flicks the bails off
he bowls a quicker one on the off, the batsman digs it out to the bowler
another fuller legspinning delivery on off stump, defended off the front foot
the umpire is checking for a stumping! This was a typical quick legspinner that whizzes past the outside edge. But Marlon never lifted his back foot
another quicker legspinner, beats the batsman's forward prod. He is looking very uncomfortable out there. Fortunately for him, it's the end of the over
he comes forward and slices the length delivery down to third man
he bowls a full delivery outside off, it keeps going away with the angle and Marlon, who is hanging his bat way away from his body, is beaten
this time he pulls his bat in late as the ball is just outside off
comes forward and dabs the length delivery to point
he stays in the crease, shuffles a little towards off and defends the length delivery to off side
he is off the mark with a little steer to third man. He played that one from the crease too although the ball was not short at all.. No feet movement yet
slower and loopy this time, the batsman comes forward and defends it to point
now a quicker one, drifting on to the pads, Samuels pushes it back to the bowler
slower delivery now, the batsman came forward to defend, but played outside the line.. A shout for lbw, but there was some bat on that
flatter and quicker this time, the batsman defends it down the pitch
beautiful release here, tossed up, slower and drifting in. Samuels defends it to off
full and on the stumps, Samuels digs it out towards long on for a single
he bowls a fuller delivery outside off, Samuels comes forward and defends it to off
he bowls a slower one this time, on a length outside off, the batsman again comes forward and defends it to point
he bowls this one full and on the pads, the batsman gets in a tangle as he was moving towards the off side, misses the ball, but that was going down leg
slower delivery on off, the batsman defends it to off

loose shot and it almost results in his downfall! It was full on off and Bravo goes to drive without moving forward, the ball shapes in and takes the inside edge and goes perilously past the leg stump
he defends it solidly back down the pitch this time
tossed up and full on the stumps, drift in, the batsman drives it down to long on
full delivery on the stumps, Bravo digs it out back to the bowler
hello hello! Lala bowls a real long hop and pitches it on the margins of the pitch.. very close to the grass. Bravo stretches out and instead of leaving it, pushes it past point
he finds his radar again, quicker and on off, defended to off
slower leg spinner on off stump, the batsman defends it off the back foot
another leg spinning delivery on off stump, the batsman defends and drinks are called
but he starts off with a good offspinning delivery that beats the bat
flatter and quicker on off, the batsman defends it solidly to off
tossed up delivery outside off, the batsman comes forward and defends it to short third man
tossed up a touch wide outside off, Lil Bravo opens up and drives it to deep point
tossed up delivery on off, hits the pad, but that was spinning down leg
slightly short and turns in, allows the batsman to get back and tuck it to square leg for a single
he draws the batsman forward with the flight, the batsman then defends it to off
slower and loopier and on off, Samuels defends it again
bowls this from wide of the crease, it's fuller on off. The batsman drives it hard, but can't beat the man at cover
slightly shorter outside off, Samuels goes on the back foot to punch it through off, but the ball comes a touch slow off the deck, messes the batsman's timing
quicker and drifting down the leg side, the batsman misses and is hit on the pads
he comes forward and gets some bat on this drifter, takes a single to square leg
he is getting some turn, this one from wide outside off. Samuels defends off the front foot
he goes on the back foot and nudges a quicker delivery to backward square leg
tossed up and full, Lil Bravo drives it firmly, but straight to cover
tossed up and much slower, the batsman comes forward and defends it solidly
now a quicker one outside off, the shortness in length allows Lil Bravo to go back and punch it firmly to deep point
the batsman tries to whip a turning delivery to the leg side, but this spins down the leg side
he goes down on his knees and sweeps the quicker delivery on his pads down to fine leg
quicker and full, drifting in too, Samuels drives it to long on
slightly short outside off, but it turns into the batsman, who taps it to backward square leg for a single
quicker and shorter, turns away a touch, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
he goes on the back foot and pushes the length delivery to cover
quicker delivery on the pads, Samuels tucks it to deep backward square leg to bring up the team's hundred
flighted and on the middle stump, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up, the batsman comes out of the crease and pushes it to cover
flatter one outside off, the batsman steers it to short third man for a single
a quick dab towards cover and they show first sign of intent in running, they make it easily
he waits in the crease and pushes it towards backward point for another easy single

way quicker this time and Lil Bravo chooses to go on the back foot for a cut when it wasn't that short. He gets an outside edge that goes between the keeper and the slip fielder, down to the boundary and Lil Bravo gets to his half-century
tossed up delivery on the pads, too full, the batsman drives it to wide long on
tossed up delivery on off, the batsman pushes it past the non-striker for a single
he comes forward and drives the flighted delivery back to the bowler
tossed up again, drifting in to the pads this time, the batsman pushes it to midwicket

quicker slider this time, the batsman gets hit on the pads, the bowler appeals for lbw, the batsman looks down the ground, but Umar Akmal quickly tries to flick the ball back to stumps. He misses and it was heading down the leg side as well
he goes on the back foot and pushes the flatter delivery to point
quicker delivery on off, Bravo again dabs it to cover point for a quick single
tossed up and really full, the batsman drives it firmly to mid off
he threatens to come down the pitch, but stays back and defends it down the pitch
he comes forward and drives the flighted delivery back to the bowler
quicker delivery on the off stumps, the batsman pushes it to midwicket
he stays stuck in the crease and defends the flighted delivery to midwicket
flatter and quicker, some turn away from the batsman too, Bravo cuts it to short third man
this time he comes forward and defends it to backward point
much slower this time, the batsman comes right forward and defends it to point
fires this on the pads and he appeals for lbw as the batsman gets hit on the thigh pad while playing the sweep, would have probably hit the leg stump, but the umpire says no
quick and it spins down the leg side, goes between Umar Akmal's pads and down to the boundary
he comes forward and pushes the tossed up delivery to cover
the short leg fielder dives to his right to keep the batsman in his crease after he had played the ball with the turn to the leg side
he goes on the back foot and punches the flatter delivery to deep cover
tossed up and Samuels drives it almost to the hands of mid-off, reaches the fielder just after bouncing in front.. He takes the single and breaks myth's myth

he comes forward and pushes the flighted delivery to the off side for a quick single, but Lil Bravo is down on the ground now.. The throw from the cover fielder was fired towards the non-striker's end and it hits Lil Bravo's left wrist. He writhes in pain and the physio comes running down with his magic bag.
there are shouts of 'catch it' again as the batsman comes down the pitch and drives it in the air through wide mid off
he tucks it to square leg this time
goes on the back foot and creates some room too, chops it on to point

it's over! Saeed Ajmal gets his third West Indies wicket within a month! This one was the doosra, tossed up on off, the batsman tries to drive it expecting it to spin away, but this one keeps coming in, drives through the gap between the bad and pad and splays the stumps.
tossed up delivery on off stump, the batsman comes forward and squeezes it to deep point for a single
he gets hit on the pads with the one that turns in sharply from outside off, the ball rolls behind square on the leg side
he takes a long forward stride to defend, gets hit on the pads as the ball turns in
loud appeal for lbw as this one hits the pad again and beats the batsman in his forward stride, but he was struck outside the line of stumps
slightly short and Simmons goes on the back foot and guides it fine on the off side
quicker and flatter outside off, the batsman goes back and punches it through cover for a couple
tossed up delivery on the stumps, Marlon drives it to long on for a single
he stays in the crease and works the full delivery to midwicket

on the leg stump and the batsman immediately goes down on his knee to sweep, the keeper moves down the leg side and manages to get some pad on it to stop the boundary.. Umar says he played a little football there
the batsman comes forward to a quicker delivery and defends
flatter and quicker on the stumps, defended off the back foot
tossed up delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and drives it to deep extra cover
slightly short in length, but it keeps sliding in with the arm, the batsman manages to cut it late and fine on the off side for a couple of runs
he comes forward and pushes the quicker delivery back to the bowler
slower this time and outside off, Simmons opens the face and runs it down fine for a single
this one turns away after pitching on back of length, the batsman punches it to backward point for a single
comes forward and guides the length delivery to short third man
he bowls a flatter one on off from round the wicket, the batsman tucks it to backward square leg
shorter and quicker on the stumps, the batsman tucks it to square leg this time

the offstump is knocked back! Samuels was struggling to deal with Ajmal's bag of tricks, so he tries one of his own. He moves way outside leg stump, but sees his trick fail as the bowler bowls a quick one on off. Samuels tries to run it down to off, but misses and loses his offstump. End of misery.
flatter offspinning delivery on off stump, the batsman defends it to the short leg fielder
quicker delivery on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
top-edged over the keeper's head, the slip fielder and the fine leg fielder try to do a little relay thingy, which goes bad and they allow a single
shorter delivery outside off, Bravo pushes it straight to cover
tossed up and full on off stump, the batsman clears his front foot out and drives it down the ground to long off
here come the slider, it hits the inside edge and goes to backward square leg for a single. Lala has his hands on his head..
another quicker one on the middle stump, the batsman defends it to off
slower and wide outside off, spinning away too, Bravo chops it to cover without any timing
he comes forward and pushes it to midwicket for a quick single
tossed up on middle and leg from round the stumps, jabbed past short leg
flighted fuller, but slips down leg this time as Bravo misses the sweep
that was a chance, a very difficult one, Hafeez's initial movement at slip was to lean to his right as Bravo shaped for the cut to one close on off stump, the thick edge flew to Hafeez's left instead
pops up onto the pitch as he comes forward to defend, but before short leg can get to it
quicker and fuller, clipped back to the bowler
blocked down the track
wants the single as he pushes an offbreak towards extra cover, but there is no run there
pushes forward at one angled in, it pops backwards to short fine leg
tossed up full outside off, pushed to point
this hurried on from a good length, he was on the backfoot looking for the cut, but could not place it past point
worked to midwicket who cannot prevent the single as he lets it slip past his dive

Afridi with another of those celebrations, Umar Akmal has raced to square leg and dived to hold onto this top-edged sweep, Simmons saw it flighted on middle and leg, bent down and gave the sweep a crack, the ball bounced more than he'd budgeted for
pushes a flighted overpitched ball past the non-striker to long on, keeper shouts khud hi Lala (field it yourself) but it was well wide of the bowler
ovepitched on middle, Pollard is away with a nudge to midwicket
worked with the spin to deep square
pushes a flatter one down to long on
hello, that didn't get up at all, spun in, hit the base of the pad, and rolled down leg
pushed back to the bowler
135.8 kph, good length delivery zipping across not far from off stump, left alone
ptiched up to the pads, worked to deep square leg
comes forward and pushes it in front of extra cover for a comfortable single in the end
nasty, that reared at Pollard from back of a length and left him too, fortunate not to glove it, helped himself by not jabbing
bouncer, ducked under
back of a length, but on the leg side, and is nudged fine for a couple
paddles a full delivery but cannot beat short fine leg
quick and spinning in, worked to midwicket
Umar overdoing the "khud hi" now, no way Hafeez could have stopped that push going in the direction of long on
flatter, and just outside off, Bravo is very quick to rock back and slap it to the deep cover rope
cannot do much with the sweep, will take the single to short fine
short and wide, he arches back in typical style and cuts, but does not get enough on it, in the air to the sweeper
there is no one at slip now, Pollard opens the face late and runs a bouncing delivery past the keeper, third man gets around to it
can;t get the single as he pushes a length ball, Hafeez at backward point runs forward to deny him
width, Bravo hops and tries dabbing it to third man, misses, bowler thinks there was an edge, no reaction from the keeper, and the umpire
Afridi is not as quick anymore, and a nudge behind square leg produces two as he runs in from fine leg
short, around off stump, but Bravo's pulled it hard in the air to the deep midwicket boundary, on one leg as he connects
length ball worked to midwicket off the pad
jabs forward, an inside edge rolls to short fine leg
tossed up very full on the pad, forced to long on
makes some room but this is right on off stump, and he can only guide it to point for one
that looked close, Pollard caught on the pad on the forward push as Ajmal straightened it from round the stumps, ball tracker has it pitching middle and hitting leg stump, Pollard lucky
low full toss, he goes after it, but finds mid off
guided behind point, third man gets around as they take two
tries to go behind point again, but this is a slower one, and Bravo is beaten
superb delivery, there is an appeal for caught behind, but umpire Nero says no, it jagged and bounced across Bravo, who pushed and was beaten
sends it far down leg from a good length
full toss on middle, turned straight to midwicket, second full toss he's missed out on this over
yorker on middle, Bravo turns it to midwicket, who misses with the throw
tossed up and spins in to middle, pushed back
could have been a possible stumping chance as Bravo missed this one spinning down leg, but keeper could not collect cleanly
walks down, smothers it, and they go through before Ajmal can get to the ball
he's powered this overpitched ball , Ajmal's got his leg out of the way, and long on's dive is in vain
slogs and misses one that jags across him, there is an appeal for stumping, but Pollard's got his back leg inside the crease in time
nudges it square off the pad
Pollard cleared front leg, and had a heave, but missed the full delivery outside off
that's in his zone, slower one pitched up, outside off, Pollard reaches out and whacks it over the umpire
Riaz loses it, as he often does, sprays this light years outside off
tried swatting this length ball straight down the ground, but didn't time it
another length ball, outside off, Pollard swings big, and the ball disappears into the sightscreen
overpitched widish, Pollard tries squeezing it behind point, but the fielder dives and saves runs
now Bravo, Riaz bowls in the same area, pitching it up outside off, and Bravo drills it over extra cover, it bounces just inside
backs away too much outside leg, it is the straighter one, and he missed by a long margin
offbreak now, cramps him completely as he stays put and it hurries onto middle
harmless length ball on the pads, Pollard is glad to get off strike against Ajmal with just a nudge to short fine leg
comes forward and nudges from off to square leg, they push for the second and make it easily
spins and bounces down the leg side, Bravo misses
tickles a full delivery, short fine leg dives
scythes an overpitched ball wide of the sweeper
oh dear, starts with a skiddy pitched up ball that is fine on pace but is directed down the leg side, Umar's dive cannot prevent all the byes
it's flying, it's flying, all the way to backward square leg, Bravo's heave has him lose his bat, he's missed the ball, and Umar has conceded a bye
he attempts the yorker again, and gets it spot-on, right on middle stump, Pollard brought down his mighty club on it, but difficult to hit those
superb recovery from Asad Ali, another yorker, slight inswing, Pollard tries to go off side, misses, and loses his off stump
around the blockhole again, Asad Ali's radar is on steroids, Sammy turns it through midwicket
a whip from off takes the ball through square leg, but they are kept to one
lost it this time, hurled it miles outside off
a full toss on the pads, Sammy misses out, Irfan scrambles to his right at short fine leg
super start, 140 kph yorker curling into middle and leg, Sammy backs away and bangs the bat down on it
Bravo misses a very low full toss outside off now
slower one goes wrong down leg, but Umar Akmal's ensured West Indies don't steal a bye, he's hit the stumps, and Sammy's dive has him inches short

Umar Akmal has conjured another run-out, Roach had to get Bravo on strike, he jammed bat down on a yorker and ran, Umar did not lob this time, he ran all the way to the stumps and beat the returning batsman
steered to third man
Bravo heaves at a full toss, thick edge flies fine to the third man rope
Riaz ends with one more around the blockhole, outside off, Bravo squeezes it to point

inn2.comm: starts off with a quick short of length delivery on off, the batsman defends off the back foot
keeps it just outside the off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
he comes half-forward to a length delivery and slices it to point
takes a tiny step forward to a fuller delivery and pushes it to cover
length delivery outside off, it hits the inside half of the bat as the batsman comes forward to defend
starts off with a maiden as Jamshed defends the back of length delivery to point
he starts off with a full delivery on off stump, the batsman defends it down the pitch
length delivery in the channel outside off, doesn't get up much, left alone
length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward tentatively and pushes it to the leg side
he keeps bowling a full length outside off, the batsman comes half-forward and defends
now West Indies start from where Pakistan left, Holder bowls a wide delivery down the leg side and it was too far away from Charles
length delivery aimed at the top of off, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
invites a drive with a fuller delivery on off, the batsman though is unable to find the gap, hits it straight to cover
teases the batsman with a quick one wide outside off. Jamshed chases it and is beaten
this time he comes forward to push at a length delivery, but this one keeps going away with the angle and beats the bat again
he decides to let this one go through, the keeper takes it low around his ankles
he comes forward to a fuller length delivery and defends it solidly to cover
he walks a step across, but Roach shortens the length, Jamshed has no room for his shot and he ends up defending
length delivery on off, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
he chooses to leave this length delivery, but it keeps coming in with the angle and just misses the off stump..Some will say good leave, some will say he didn't have any idea about it
he comes forward this time and defends the length delivery to point
stays in the crease and pushes a length delivery to mid-on
length delivery outside off, the batsman lets this one go through
he gets up on his toes and pushes the back of length delivery to cover
teasing line and length outside off, the batsman comes forward then leaves it alone
length delivery outside off, 140 ks, the batsman defends it solidly to the off side
he tries the jailbreak! Tries to charge Roach and smash him over midwicket, misses it completely..Roach smiles, with his hands on head
this one now whizzes past the outside edge.. Good pressure by WI bowlers
length delivery, more back foot defence.. Where is the first run going to come from?
Overthrow? No, Simmons does well backing up for a quick throw from point after Jamshed had pushed it to Pollard's right
and, drumroll... another maiden, length ball defended back to the bowler
some runs, another wide down the leg side
length delivery from atop a two-storey building, the batsman defends it off the front foot
nothing else was working, so Shehzad gives the bowler a charge, the bowler shortens the length, but Shehzad slaps it over cover anyway. The ball slows down in the heavy outfield
now this one is too cute at the moment. It is a length delivery on off and the batsman tries to play it to fine leg, gets hit on the top of his pads, but that was going over
pushes it with soft hands towards mid on and calls for a quick single
gets good bounce from a length, the batsman defends it to point, taking his bottom hand off the handle
he stays in the crease and defends the length ball to off
he bowls a short of length delivery, the batsman drops it to his boots
angles it from wide of the crease, the batsman defends it towards cover off the front foot
keeps it full from wide of the crease, the batsman plays it right under his nose as he defends it to off
fuller delivery on the off stump line, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
length delivery on off, the batsman pushes it back to the pitch
another maiden for Roach, he fires it full on the stumps, the batsman pushes it back to him

dropped by Dwayne Bravo! He juggles a few times, three four times at second slip, but is not able to hold on to it. Jamshed chased a full delivery and a healthy edge flew to Bravo, but he fails to grab on
and now he gets his first runs with a drive through covers
he is moving now, he is alive, this time he flicks a length delivery past midwicket for another couple
length delivery on off, the batsman defends it off the back foot
length delivery angled across the left-hander, the batsman lets it go through
they are coming in doubles now, it's too straight for Jamshed and he flicks it past midwicket again
he bowls a back of length delivery, the batsman defends it to off
full delivery on the pads, the batsman pushes it straight to mid on
now he swings his bat as he sees the length ball angling towards him, doesn't get hold of it completely, but manages to slap it over midwikcet
he comes forward and defends the length ball solidly to off
holy moly! Where did that come from? He took a step down the pitch, Roach shortens the length, but Jamshed just pulls it over deep midwicket for a superbly time hit.. sails over the rope easily
now he defends the length delivery to off
he makes room to slap the length delivery, but hits it straight to cover point
now Shehzad pulls it over deep midwicket! It was not that short but Shehzad was ready in a fraction of a second, he swivels and sends it soaring
return of confidence! He charges down the pitch and drives the full delivery, straight to cover
he bowls it full, but on the pads, Shehzad flicks it to deep midwicket for a single
length delivery on off, Jamshed stays calm and defends it solidly
he comes forward and drives the length delivery to mid on
he bowls it from wide of the crease, but it's too straight and slightly short of length, the batsman whips it off his hips to deep backward square leg
length delivery aimed at the middle stump, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
another short of length delivery on the middle stump line, the batsman whips it to deep midwicket for an easy couple

here comes the wicket! Unlike the last few deliveries that were heading for the stumps, Roach bowls this one outside off. Shehzad hangs his bat at that and doesn't move his feet at all. No problems for the umpire as that made a nice woody sound en route to the keeper's gloves
he edges the first delivery to third man, not the shot of a man in form. But he did come forward positively to that length delivery
Roach appeals for a caught behind chance, but the cordon remains quiet.. That one again whizzed past the outside edge like it has all day
he bowls it short and wide outside off, easy pickings for Professor, he cuts it hard through point
tossed up delivery outside off, the batsman stretches out and pushes it to deep cover

he turns it like a top! Tossed up on off, then it grips the surface and turns a mile past the bat, the batsman falls over a bit, could have been a close stumping chance but Charles took some time to control that
another offbreak, not much turn this time, the batsman defends it to off
he pushes it to deep point for a single this time
tossed up delivery on off, the batsman defends it off the front foot
he starts off with a length delivery on off, the batsman defends it to cover
even he gets the ball to cut away from the pitch, but Nasir plays a loose shot and is beaten. He was trying to whip it the leg side
length delivery on off and middle, Jamshed tucks it to wide mid-on with ease for a single
he bowls it slightly short of length, the batsman defends it to midwicket
angled to off and middle stump, the batsman comes forward and tucks it to square leg
excellent drive! Sammy's pace is ideal too. Jamshed sees fuller length outside off, he plants his front foot out and drives it all along the ground through extra cover
flighted delivery on off, the batsman defends it to the leg side
tossed up on the middle stump line, the batsman defends it off the front foot
that was a good ball, Hafeez wanted to play it towards the leg side, but gets squared up as it goes the other way
defends the regular offbreak to square leg
now the other one, turns away after pitching on leg stump, the batsman dabs it towards square leg and calls for a quick single
bowls one outside off that spins away from Jamshed, who lets it go through
oh superbly crunched off the back foot! It was short of length and came slow of the pitch, Hafeez arched back and punched it through cover point
he comes forward to a length delivery and defends it to midwicket
more resolute defence again, this time he pushes it to the off side

oye! Is that close? I think Jamshed has made it to the striker's end. There was some hesitation as Hafeez pushed it to wide mid-off and set off immediately. Jamshed was slow to respond, but managed to beat Roach's direct hit
length delivery outside off, the batsman defends it off the front foot
he comes forward again and defends the length delivery down the pitch
tossed up delivery on off stump, the batsman pushes it to point off the front foot for a single
oh he is lucky! He gets a big leading edge towards mid-off, but the fielder is back at the boundary. He wanted to play that towards midwicket
tossed up delivery, the batsman defends it down the pitch
he stays on the back foot and nudges the length delivery to square leg for a single
he comes forward to the flighted ball, but gets a thick outside edge towards backward point
now he gets to the pitch of the delivery and drives it to extra cover
short of length delivery outside off, the batsman is beaten as he tries to cut this one from too close to his body
length delivery outside off, the batsman defends it to point
back of length delivery just outside off, he punches it to the fielder at point again
he tries to force this length delivery through the off side without moving his feet, but gets a thick inside edge past his stumps. The ball held up on the pitch was an extra moment
length delivery on off stump, this time he defends it from the crease
goes on the back foot and tucks the length delivery to deep midwicket for a single
the thesis remains incomplete! He charges down the track, is not to the pitch of the delivery, but carries on with the lofted shot, gets it a touch high on the bat and holes out to long on .
tossed up delivery on off stump, Jamshed takes a forward stride and pushes it to mid-off
big turn outside off, the batsman tries to cut it, but that turns and bounces, zips past the outside edge
slower this time, the batsman comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
flighted delivery on off stump, Jamshed smothers the spin
another quicker one that spins away sharply, but unlike last time, Jamshed is beaten by the low bounce this time
loud appeal for lbw as Misbah comes forward to defend the length delivery. The bat and the pad were close together, but Misbah had taken a good stride forward
he tries to tuck the length delivery to the leg side, but gets hit on the thigh pad
takes another positive stride and drives the length delivery, but straight to cover
he bowls it full on off stump, Misbah comes forward again and drives it to cover
repeat from Misbah, takes a forward stride and drives to cover
this time, just for the sake of doing something different, drives it to midwicket
dropped, thick edge low to Sammy at slip, and he fails to hold on, then the throw from short third man misses, Misbah would have been gone without scoring otherwise
another edge, it is the straighter one from round the stumps, Misbah is opened up, but this time it falls short of slip
full, worked to midwicket
defended from the crease
almost another one, Misbah is having problems with the straighter one from round the stumps, Sammy thinks there was an edge through to the keeper
back of a length, blocked
opens the face and runs a length ball to point
pushes wide of mid on with a slightly closed face and goes through with the single
cramped for room with the incoming angle, and guides it to point
Misbah gets off the mark in typical fashion after a succession of dot balls, lifts a length ball from outside off cleanly over midwicket, one bounce over the rope
bangs it in short but also overcooks the angle, carries down leg
Jamshed has to head back after Misbah turns one from off to midwicket, throw misses, else Jamshed was in trouble
a long hop, he pulls it but deep square leg's dive saves the boundary
that didn't get up, came in to off around the ankles, Misbah did really well to keep it out
keeps low again, is turned to square leg
blocked off the front foot
Misbah is ready for the reverse sweep before the ball is bowled, even though slip moves to his right, he hits it wide of him, and also beats third man
moves across and nudges in front of square leg, Jamshed is not the quickest, but he makes it
hits the pads and rolls away as he moves across and misses
mistimes a punch to midwicket
tight line on off, an inside edge rolls onto the crease  as Misbah defends
leans forward to push to extra cover
moves around in the crease but Sammy is right around off and Misbah can only push it away
gets forward and works a pitched up ball to long on
slapped away straight to extra cover
hurled full at 89 kph, turned to midwicket
worked past square leg for one
short from Samuels and Jamshed rocks back to slam it over midwicket
mishits off the back foot to long off
comes across and defends a 93 kph length ball
drives an overpitched ball to long off
shuffles across and turns a full delivery to long on
slogs at an overpitched delivery, thick inside edge races past the stumps, Narine slides to save the boundary at fine leg
goes across, Sasmmy is right on the stumps, Misbah is cramped and pushes it back
on middle and leg, turned to deep midwicket
pushed to short extra cover
nudges square to the leg side and sprints for the single, throw misses
quick and on off stump, defended from the crease
tries to force it off the back foot but mishits it into the ground
worked in front of square leg, Misbah is happy with one
nudged with the spin to fine leg

dropped by Gayle running to his right from mid on, Jamshed escapes again, he wanted to pull one that hurried onto him, swirled high over the bowler, Gayle ran and dived, got both hands to the ball but could not hold on
Jamshed is surviving everything, now a dive has him just inside  as Charles breaks a stump in trying to run him out, they'd aborted the single after a cut behind point
turned to forward square leg, who cannot stop it and concedes the single
slower one mistimed to mid on
moves forward and eases a length ball to extra cover
gets a boundary off a a thick edge now, goes reaching for an angled ball, there is no one at slip
backs away but turns a full one to midwicket
makes room again, Samuels hurls it in full, Misbah forces it to covers
goes hard but cannot get much bat on this full delivery, takes the single towards point
pushed off the front foot to cover
powerfully hit to extra cover
skids on and does not get up much, he pulls to deep midwicket
slogged out to deep square leg
tight line on off, he comes across and runs it to point
played out to midwicket
Misbah's gone, Sammy's smiling, he was making room outside leg often, missed a length ball as he tried to cut, Sammy was spot-on as always, and off stump was rattled
across to defend to short mid on
right forward to block to extra cover
pushed through full outside off, pushed to extra cover
very full, pushed back
tosses it up and pushes it wider, Jamshed reaches out and lofts over extra cover
nudged in front of square leg, by the time the deep fielders run in, they've taken two
pitched up, pushed to extra cover
width, but he;s hit it straight to cover
comes in from a good length and he mistimes the punch to midwicket
sends it quick and well down leg, Charles does well to collect it
some width offered from a good length, Shafiq takes toll, crashing it to the deep cover boundary
reverts to the off stump line, Shafiq defends
full and down the leg side once more, umpire Nero does not call a wide
punched off the back foot straight to mid off
attempt a cut and misses, the shot was on
goes intentionally over extra cover, and it falls safely to the left of the sweeper running in
pushed through down the leg side at 9.2 kph
lunges forward to defend back to the bowler
worked to square leg for a single
moves across and works from outside off, deep square leg runs in to keep them to one
turned past midwicket, in the air for a while, to long on
Jamshed can;t get out today, he's survived yet again, Charles has fluffed the stumping, he's failed to collect the ball after Jamshed walked past a quicker one
drives an overpitched ball to long on
tucked off the pad to deep square leg
worked to midwicket
whips this length ball straight to square leg
turns a pitched up ball between short mid on and the non-striker to long on
oh dear, Shafiq could have hit this long hop anywhere, instead he rocks back and slaps it straight to extra cover
played out to midwicket off the front foot
tries a sweep second ball and is hit on the pad, there is an appeal but this was going down
quick and straight, Umar drives hard and a thick edge flies past slip
sends it down leg this time
this turns in and bounces, Umar takes it on the body
has him reaching out to one outside off, and pushing to covers
hits a pitched up ball hard back to the bowler
Jamshed reaches fifty with all those lives, picks a length ball from off stump and lofts it with a closed face over mid on
guides this length ball to point
Jamshed could have been in trouble, but for that to happen, Roach at mid on had to stop the ball, it went right through him
pushes a length ball to extra cover
squeezes out a yorker to backward point
full from round the stumps, nudged square
spin and bounce beats the attempted cover drive
a leading edge pops up in front of point, confusion in the running before they get back
goes after it and ends up slicing an offbreak just out of the reach of cover
punches the straighter one to cover
nudged to backward square leg off the pad
flicks from off behind square leg

finally a catch has been held off Jamshed's bat, he's lifted this pitched up delivery, angled across him, from off stump line over midwicket., Roach has run to his left and dived to take an outstanding catch
jags in from outside off, is punched down the ground
walks down the pitch first ball, is hit on the pad, wants the run, midwicket is on the ball and Afridi turns back
walks out again and defends properly this time
he'd made room and was ready to swing, but saw he could not quite get under this one, and adjusted to guide it to point
works a full ball to midwicket
finds square leg now, can;t get the run
full and on the pad, defended off the front foot
this was hurrying and straightening on off stump, Umar still was able to find timing on the cut, Holder is clumsy in getting down at point and lets it through
quicker one, Umar was opening up but had to defend
pushed down to long on for a single
slower one pitched up around off, pushed back to the bowler
not that short, he drags a pull over midwicket, there is a man in the deep too
here comes Afridi, skips out and lifts this over the non-striker, but long on scrambles across to save the boundary just in time
hes coming out every ball to Pollard, who drops it short now, and it pops up square on the leg side
slower one punched to long on
walks outside off stump, Pollard slows it down, Afridi guides it behind point
he backs away several feet to leg, but this is the carrom ball and it spins away from his swing
and again, tossed up carrom ball spins across his big swing outside leg
nudges an offbreak to square leg
worked to midwicket
that will be it for today, Narine raises his arms as the crowd celebrates, it is the other one again, Afridi charges out and heaves, misses, and Charles completes the stumping
quick and going across the right-hander, stabbed away to point
bowls a length delivery on off, Umar eases it to long on for a single
he goes wide of the crease and bowls a slower length ball, the batsman is beaten as he attempts a late cut
he bowls it full from wide of the crease, the batsman defends it to midwicket
he nudges it to square leg for a single
he takes a forward stride and drives a widish length ball to long-off
he bowls a slower delivery from wide of the crease, the batsman guides it to short fine leg and a throw is fired in. Had it hit, the batsmen would have struggled
fires it on the middle stump line, the batsman goes on the back foot and tucks it to deep midwicket

tossed up delivery, slower this time. The batsman comes forward and tries to turn it to leg side, but gets hit right in front.. A good shout for lbw, but the umpire doesn't concur. That was a good shout indeed, as the replays show, that it would have gone on to hit the middle stump
this time, it's a quicker one. The batsman tries to turn it to leg, but it turns the other way, and he gets a leading edge to off
he comes forward and defends it to midwicket
this time, it is wide down the leg side
he comes forward and drives it firmly to the fielder at cover
offspinning delivery on off and middle, the batsman gets hit on the pads, but that would have gone over the top
they take a quick single with a dab to point
he makes room and tries to whack the length delivery to the off side, but is beaten by the lack of pace in that one
this time he comes forward and drives it hard to the off side, but straight to the man at cover
he drags the length delivery on off to deep midwicket with a back foot mow
a surprising and quick yorker from Pollard, Wahab digs it out in time
he fires it on the pads this time, Wahab gets an inside edge on to his pads and it rolls to the left of the keeper

Too good for Wahab, it has squeezed in from the little available space and has knocked the leg stump. That's wicket no. 3 for Narine! Wahab was shaping for the sweep, but is too late to bring his bat down to a quick missile fired in by Narine. The ball gets under his bat and pad before he can kneel down, strikes his stumps, the batsman slips and is left mourning on the floor
he pulls a shortish delivery to deep midwicket to open his account
he makes room and slaps a length delivery over the umpire's head for a single to long on

caught at slip! Ajmal gets the taste of his own medicine! It was full on off and much like me, Ajmal had no idea which way this was going. It takes the outside edge and Sammy takes a good sharp low catch at first slip
it is the other one, but it's slightly short, allows the batsman time to adjust and defend
it's the conventional offbreak and it spins towards the pads, hits the batsman's pads and slips between the keeper's pads
he drives it towards wide long on and calls for a second immediately, Asad Ali makes it back in the time
makes room again and waits for the slower delivery, then cuts it past short third man for a couple
length delivery on off, Umar pushes it to extra cover and calls for a quick one
short delivery outside off for Asad first up, and the batsman is beaten as he tries to guide it fine on off. He is not impressed with himself for missing out on that shot
throws his bat at this fuller one and ends up slicing it towards cover for a single
he makes room by moving outside leg and drives it to long-off to keep the strike
he bowls a full delivery outside off, the batsman drives it to long-off for a single
a good yorker and it hits the batsman's shoes en route to the keeper, struck him outside the line of leg stump
now he charges down the pitch, but the offcutter goes between his bat and pad
another slower ball, the line is just outside leg stump and the batsman manages to get some bat on it to guide it fine on the leg side
full delivery on off stump, the batsman drives it firmly to long off
goes for the big slog, but he is too early as the ball arrives a little after he is done with the swing.
he bowls a full delivery on the stumps, the batsman digs it out to midwicket
now he finds a boundary with a flat batter forceful swat through cover, there was no one in the deep
more smart stuff from Umar. He was expecting a full delivery, goes down on his knee and ramps it fine on the leg side
a slower and low full toss on the middle stump, Umar is off balance as he is retreating to the leg side, but he manages to slice it past the diving backward point fielder
now he swats the length delivery down to deep backward square leg to hand over the strike to Asad
he swings his bat, but makes no connection as he has played too early to the slower delivery
he gets his front leg out of the way and tries to whack the slower delivery, but ends up dragging it to square leg
he moves outside leg stump and punches the length delivery to off, but he finds the man at cover

oh wow! He charges out and throws the kitchen sink at this length delivery, whacks it very high over deep midwicket. Holder at the boundary gets a hand to it, but parries it over.. That's his half-century as well
oh no, he has fallen immediately after getting to his landmark! And with that, Pakistan have lost their final hope. He goes after a length delivery, but holes out at long-off
It's game over! Asad Ali, with not much left, comes down the pitch and gives it all with a heave, but only gets it as far as Pollard at deep midwicket
